                <head>No. 19.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">C. J. McCarthy</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">C. B. Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Honolulu, Hawaiian Islands</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">C. B. Wilson</hi>:</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: As per your request of to-day I inclose you
                    a diagram of the position of the <hi rend="italic">Boston</hi> troops as of
                    Monday evening, January 16, 1893. They remained in the third position for
                    several days.</p>
                <figure>
                    <graphic url="figure_1071"/>
                </figure>
                <p>In connection with the arrival of the committee of safety, I would say that they
                    arrived at the Government building at 2:30 p.m. on <pb facs="1072" n="1066"
                        xml:id="pg_1066"/> Tuesday, January 17, loitered about the corridor a few
                    minutes, asked Mr. Hossinger for possession of the building, and then Mr. Cooper
                    proceeded to read the proclamation. He finished same at 2:10 p.m., at which time
                    I received your telephone message and came to the station house.</p>
                <p>Yours, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. J. McCarthy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
